Basic Ubuntu Linux Commands
1. File and Directory Commands

ls

Lists files and folders in the current directory.

ls -l

Shows detailed list with permissions and size.

ls -a

Shows all files including hidden ones.

pwd

Displays the current working directory path.

cd foldername

Moves into a directory.

cd ..

Moves one step back (to parent folder).

cd /path/to/folder

Moves to a specific path.

mkdir foldername

Creates a new directory.

rmdir foldername

Deletes an empty directory.

rm filename

Deletes a file.

rm -r foldername

Deletes a folder and all its contents.

2. File Handling Commands

touch filename

Creates an empty file.

cp source destination

Copies a file.

cp -r sourcefolder destination

Copies a folder.

mv oldname newname

Renames or moves a file or folder.

cat filename

Displays file content.

nano filename

Opens file in nano text editor.

vim filename

Opens file in vim editor.

3. System and Information Commands

uname -a

Shows system information.

top

Shows running processes.

htop

Improved process viewer (if installed).

df -h

Shows disk usage.

du -sh foldername

Shows size of a folder.

free -h

Shows memory usage.

uptime

Shows system running time.

4. Permissions and Ownership

chmod 755 filename

Changes file permissions.

chmod +x filename

Makes a file executable.

chown user:group filename

Changes file owner.

5. Package Management (APT)

sudo apt update

Updates package list.

sudo apt upgrade

Upgrades all installed packages.

sudo apt install packagename

Installs a package.

sudo apt remove packagename

Removes a package.

sudo apt autoremove

Removes unused dependencies.

6. Network Commands

ping hostname

Checks connectivity.

ifconfig

Shows network configuration (if installed).

ip a

Shows IP address details.

curl url

Fetches data from URL.

wget url

Downloads a file from the internet.

7. User Commands

whoami

Shows current user.

adduser username

Creates a new user.

passwd username

Changes password.

su username

Switches to another user.

8. Archive and Compression Commands

tar -cvf file.tar folder

Creates a tar archive.

tar -xvf file.tar

Extracts a tar archive.

zip file.zip file

Creates a zip file.

unzip file.zip

Extracts zip file.

9. Search and Find Commands

find /path -name "filename"

Searches for a file.

grep "text" filename

Searches for text inside a file.

grep -r "text" folder

Searches text inside a directory.

10. System Control Commands

sudo reboot

Restarts the system.

sudo shutdown now

Shuts down the system immediately.

sudo shutdown -r now

Shuts down and restarts.
